^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The 3@S bid in 2/1 has a very special meaning. It is not the same as in SAYC where it would be 16-18 with a nice 6-card suit. The idea behind 2/1 is to conserve bidding space when exploring for slam. So if you make a bid that takes up a lot of space, such as 3@S, you better have a good reason. Experts play that the 3@S bid conveys the following message:|
